<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active only in the spring and range in total length 9.5-15 mm and 2-4 mm in maximum width. Although they have been found mainly around artificial lights at night, they have also been observed feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Lonicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lonicera japonica" order="Dipsacales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Lonicera japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Gardenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gardenia jasminoides" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jasminoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Gardenia jasminoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during daytime (RP &amp; LC pers. obs.). Larval host plants include 
<taxonomicName genus="Artidesma" lsidName="Artidesma tetrandrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="tetrandrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Artidesma tetrandrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bauhinia malabarica" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="malabarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Bauhinia malabarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lecythidaceae" genus="Careya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Careya arborea" order="Polemoniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Careya arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Sterculiaceae" genus="Heritiera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heritiera minor" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Heritiera minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lythraceae" genus="Lagerstroemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lagerstroemia parviflora" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="parviflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Lagerstroemia parviflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Shorea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Shorea robusta" order="Guttiferales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Shorea robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Duffy, EAJ" journalOrPublisher="British Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B34" refString="Duffy, EAJ, 1968. A monograph of the immature stages of Oriental timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum (Natural History), London, [viii +] 434 pp. [198 figs, 18 pls]" title="A monograph of the immature stages of Oriental timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum (Natural History), London, [viii +] 434 pp. [198 figs, 18 pls]" year="1968">Duffy 1968</bibRefCitation>
